    "notes": "Phase 2 curated 2026-05-29 under curation-data-contract (Tier 1 inversion fix; replaces the prior Phase-1 unverified mass/radius). Radius/Teff/luminosity/mass anchored on Baines & Armstrong 2012 NOI interferometry (theta_LD 2.153 +/- 0.028 mas -> R 0.74 +/- 0.01 Rsun, Teff 5039 +/- 126 K via theta_LD + bolometric flux, L 0.32 +/- 0.03 Lsun, M 0.82 +/- 0.05 Msun via Yonsei-Yale isochrone); cross-checked by Di Folco 2007 CHARA/FLUOR theta_LD 2.126 +/- 0.014 mas (-> R ~0.73). No asteroseismic solution exists (the star is too active). Prior unverified values (Llop Sayson 2021 M 0.82, Rosenthal 2021 R 0.759) superseded by the interferometric anchor. [Fe/H] = Santos 2004 high-res spectroscopy -0.13 +/- 0.04 (Sousa 2008 -0.11 +/- 0.03, Gomes da Silva 2021 / Tsantaki 2013 -0.15 +/- 0.03 corroborate; all slightly sub-solar). Rotation = Croll 2006 MOST photometry, two spots P1 = 11.35 d / P2 = 11.55 d (differential rotation k ~ 0.09); Froehlich 2007 reanalysis confirms P1 = 11.348 +/- 0.037, P2 = 11.553 +/- 0.020 d, equatorial P ~ 11.2 d. Activity = Gomes da Silva 2021 AMBRE-HARPS log R'HK -4.496 (553 spectra; active K dwarf, well above the -4.9 inactive floor); X-ray Lx ~ 2e28 erg/s (XMM-Newton 0.2-2 keV, cycle-averaged, Coffaro 2020), combined with L = 0.32 Lsun (1.22e33 erg/s) giving log(Lx/Lbol) ~ -4.8; Ca II cycle 2.92 yr. AGE IS A DOCUMENTED DIVERGENCE: gyrochronology/activity indicators give a young age (Barnes 2007 gyrochronology 0.44 Gyr, adopted by Coffaro 2020; literature range 0.2-0.93 Gyr per Fuhrmann 2004 / Song 2000), recommended as consistent with the high activity + 11 d rotation, versus isochrone ages that are unreliable for cool MS dwarfs (Baines 2012 Y2 ~1 Gyr, the authors explicitly noting it is older than other studies; Valenti & Fischer 2005 ~2.6 Gyr; Gomes da Silva 2021 isochrone ~4.8 Gyr). Phase 3 must document the young-vs-isochrone split. Boyajian et al. 2012 does NOT contain eps Eri (verified absent in all VizieR tables) -- not cited despite its fame as an interferometric-radius sample."
  }
